    "created_at": "2012-04-12T21:00:02Z",
    "updated_at": "2012-04-12T21:00:02Z",
    "body": "I am of two minds.  It is true that recursive closures are almost impossible, which is a shame.  On the other hand, getting the semantics of when the capture code occurs is a pain.  In practice, if I want recursive closures, then I just create a record for the data I need and make an impl for it.  Not sure if this is an acceptable workaround.\n",
